    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early form of the Chinese clerical script that still retains many features of the seal script; was used primarily for writing office documents and for correspondence on daily matters. Examples are found among brushed writings on bamboo and wooden slips and silk manuscripts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
